<h1>{$node_name}</h1>

<p>The option “System Info” of the Menu “System” in Elastix lets us monitor the server’s hardware resources.<p>
<p>Within this option, we have two sections:</p>

<p><b>System Resources</b></p>

<p>“System Resource” shows us the values of actual use of both the memory as well as the processor.</p>

<div><img src="../modules/{$node_id}/images/system_resources_1.jpg" border="0"></div>

<ul>
<li><b>CPU Info:</b> Information about brand, model and processor speed</li>
<li><b>Uptime:</b> Time from the last reboot of the server</li>
<li><b>CPU usage:</b> Percentage of use of processor capacity</li>
<li><b>Memory usage:</b> Percentage of RAM memory utilized</li>
<li><b>Swap usage:</b> Percentage of SWAP memory utilized</li>
</ul>

<p>Here is a graphic with the statistics of simultaneous calls, percentage of use of processor and percentage of use of RAM memory.</p>

<div><img src="../modules/{$node_id}/images/system_resources_2.jpg" border="0"></div>

<p><b>Hard Drives</b></p>

<p>This section shows a summary of the utilization of storage available on the server.</p>

<div><img src="../modules/{$node_id}/images/system_resources_3.jpg" border="0"></div>

<ul>
<li><b>Partition name:</b> The name of the partition in the hard drive. Example:"HDA2"</li>
<li><b>Capacity:</b> The maximum storage capacity for the installed hard drive</li>
<li><b>Usage:</b> The percentage of the maximum storage capacity of the hard drive that has been used already</li>
<li><b>Mount point:</b> The name of the point in the filesystem where the partition is to be mounted</li>
</ul>
